Commentary: LBW! A massive wicket for Australia against the run of play! A huge appeal by the Australian players but was turned down by the umpire! Nathan Lyon bowls this short and in line with the stumps. Ollie Pope looks to go deep in the crease and tuck this off his pads but he misses. The ball hits him on the leg right in front of the wicket but it could have been pitching outside leg. Pat Cummins goes for the review nonetheless and UltraEdge shows that there is no bat involved. Ball Tracking shows this is pitching on the leg stump and there are three reds which means the onfield decision has to be reversed. Ollie Pope will be fuming with himself as this wicket falls against the run of play with England dominating proceedings so far. Australia have their second wicket and are keeping themselves in this tie.
Default_Commentary: 17.6: Nathan Lyon to Ollie Pope, OUT! lbw b Nathan Lyon.
Howout: lbw b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Australia get a crucial wicket right at the stroke of Lunch! Scott Boland bowls this slightly back of a length and just outside the off stump. He gets a bit of extra bounce and nips away from the batter as Zak Crawley looks to feel for this. There is a clear deviation but the umpire remains unmoved despite the celebrations and the appeal from the Australian players. Zak Crawley also stands his ground and after some discussion, Pat Cummins goes upstairs for the review. UltraEdge confirms that the ball clips the glove of the batter as it goes through to Alex Carey who takes a simple catch. The on-field decision has to be reversed and England have lost their third wicket. Zak Crawley has to depart after a well-made half-century but he will be disappointed that he was unable to go into the break with his wicket intact.
Default_Commentary: 26.4: Scott Boland to Zak Crawley, OUT! c Alex Carey b Scott Boland.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Scott Boland

Commentary: OUT! STUMPED! Nathan Lyon has the last laugh and he gets the big wicket of a very dangerous-looking Jonny Bairstow! Nathan Lyon bowls this short and outside the off pole but much slower in the air. Jonny Bairstow premeditates and looks to charge down the wicket but is in no position to play the shot that he wants. The ball turns and beats him on the inside edge as he is stranded well out of his crease. Alex Carey collects the ball and keeps his calm to whip the bails off in a flash. Nathan Lyon loops this one full and in line with the stumps. Moeen Ali looks to be aggressive and charges down the wicket to go aerial back down the ground. Commentary: OUT! PLUMB! England have a huge wicket here as the skipper gets a crucial breakthrough and Steven Smith has to make the long walk back to the shed! Ben Stokes was not even certain of bowling in this series but he has and has gotten rid of Australia's most accomplished batter! This is bowled on a good length and angled into the stumps from outside off. Steven Smith looks to get behind the line of the ball and block but gets beaten on the inside edge and hit flush on the pads. Ben Stokes with a loud appeal and the umpire raises the finger after a bit of contemplation. Steven Smith goes for a review straight away and feels that this is high. UltraEdge shows there is no bat involved and Ball Tracking shows three reds. Australia lose their third wicket and their review as well and England are right on top of this tie.
Default_Commentary: 26.6: Ben Stokes to Steven Smith, OUT! lbw b Ben Stokes.
Howout: lbw b Ben Stokes

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT! Moeen Ali's return to the side has been marked with a massive wicket as the man in form Travis Head has to depart right after reaching his half-century! This partnership was building nicely for Australia and just when they were looking to be in cruise-control mode, England got the breakthrough. Moeen Ali floats this one full and into the stumps. Travis Head charges down the wicket and looks to go over the infield but does not connect cleanly and hits this straight to Zak Crawley at mid-wicket. Australia lose their fourth wicket now and England have a timely wicket just before an hour's play in the second session.
Default_Commentary: 45.3: Moeen Ali to Travis Head, OUT! c Zak Crawley b Moeen Ali.
Howout: c Zak Crawley b Moeen Ali

Commentary: OUT! TIMBER! An absolute beauty from Moeen Ali and knocks Cameron Green over with a jaffa! This is looped up and bowled full, outside the off pole. He gets some vicious turn as Cameron Green looks to reach for this one and push it into the off side. The ball beats the inside edge of the bat and goes on to shatter the stumps. Commentary: OUT! BOWLED'EM! Perfect reply from Anderson after the two boundaries. Bowls it on a good length, from round the wicket and angled into the stumps from outside off. Carey gets forward to block it away but the sneaks through the gate, skims his back pad and pegs the middle stump back. Anderson breaks the a good pratnership as Carey walks back to the pavilion for a well made 66. He has 1100 first class wickets now and what a servant to the game this player has been. Australia are six wickets down now and England may sense an opening.

Commentary: OUT! TIMBER! This is some outstanding captaincy from Ben Stokes as he continued to manipulate the field and his bowlers have stuck to the task! Ollie Robinson reaps the reward for some disciplined bowling by England and it brings an end to an outstanding inning from Usman Khawaja! The crowd appreciates his effort as he departs 9 runs short of 150 runs. The field is completely unorthodox and Ollie Robinson bowls a pin-point yorker aimed for the off pole. Usman Khawaja looks to pick up the ante and gives the bowler the charge but misses the ball. The stumps are shattered and Australia lose their seventh wicket with Ollie Robinson picking up his first of this game. The hosts will now be hoping to have a go at the Australian tail.

Commentary: OUT! EDGED and TAKEN! The English players are facing the worst of these current weather conditions as the ball is suddenly doing something for the fast bowlers! Commentary: OUT! Pat Cummins has found reverse swing here and manages to uproot Ollie Pope's off pole! He bowls a well-directed yorker aimed for the stumps. Ollie Pope looks to get forward and make room for himself but is surprised by the length of the ball. He is unable to dig this one out and the ball crashes against the stumps. The attacking partnership has come to an end and England lose their third wicket. Australia needed some reprieve after England's fast start this morning and their skipper has come up with the goods. Commentary: OUT! STUMPED! Nathan Lyon has picked up a big wicket here and he punches the air in joy! Joe Root was looking ominous today and has to depart four runs short of his half-century! Nathan Lyon floats this one full and pitches on a leg-stump line. Joe Root charges down the wicket but is unable to get to the pitch of the ball. He is beaten by the sharp turn and finds himself stranded down the pitch. Alex Carey collects the ball behind the wicket and whips the bails off as England lose their fourth wicket. Australia will be thrilled and just when it looks like England will run away with the game, the claim a wicket.

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT! The short ball ploy works against Moeen Ali! The last recognised English batter is back in the hut and the hosts are eight down now. Josh Hazlewood bangs this into the pitch and angles it down the leg. Moeen Ali goes for the pull shot and gets a faint glove on this on it way to the keeper. Alex Carey takes a neat catch behind the wicket and goes up in appeal. The umpire raises his finger and Hazlewood has his first of this inning. Australia will want to go for the kill now ans get these last two wickets at the earliest as they hold the advanatge in this game at the moment.

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT! Lofted into the air and taken! Lyon gets his man and has four wickets under his belt! Ollie Robinson's fight has come to an end but he has helped push his side to a position of safety. This is floated full on the middle and leg stump line. Robinson advances down the wicket and chips this one towards Cameron Green at the long on fence. He does not have to move an inch as this goes right down his throat and he grasps hold of the ball with his bucket size hands. who comes running in and takes a fine catch. England are nine wickets down now and will still be hoping their final pair can get the lead close to 300. Australia will want this last wicket soon and go into Tea with the momentum on their side.

Commentary: OUT! EDGED and TAKEN! England are bundled out for 273, with a lead of 280 runs. Pat Cummins bowls this short of a length and outside the off pole. James Anderson looks to guide this down to third man region but gets an outside edge through to the keeper. Alex Carey goes really well diving to his left and takes a sharp catch to bring an end to England's second inning. Cummins finishes off with four wickets in this innings and Australia will be mighty pleased with their effort. England will also be relatively happy as they seem to have a fighting total on the board and conditions are bound to favor the bowlers going into the final day. It will also be TEA on DAY 4!

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! The bowling change has done the trick here and Stuart Broad has the big wicket of Marnus Labuschagne! This is a long walk back to the shed for the number one Test batter and he has had a game to forget here! Broad bowls this on a good length and outside the off pole. Marnus Labuschagne looks to poke at this one and gets a solid edge through to the keeper. Jonny Bairstow makes no mistake behind the wicket and Australia have lost their second wicket. England are clawing themselves back into this game after a good opening stand by the Australian openers.

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Edged and taken by Jonny Bairstow! Stuart Broad gets the massive wicket of Steven Smith and he is the man of the moment for England having sent Australia's two best batters back to the shed. He angles this into the stumps from outside off on a fullish length and gets the ball to move away after pitching. Smith is induced into the drive and gets a faint edge through to Bairstow behind the stumps who takes another easy catch. Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT! An expensive over from Moeen Ali but he gets his reward at the end of it and he looks absolutely thrilled! England have a massive wicket here as Travis Head has to make the long walk back and they would have known that he could have taken the game away from them in a short time. Moeen Ali bowls this slightly short and in line with the stumps. Travis Head goes onto the back foot and looks to block but the ball turns and gets his outside edge. Joe Root takes a sharp catch at slip and Australia have now lost half their side. England will feel they are on top now and the crowd definitely agrees!

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Root had put two down but he has redeemed himself. The crowd goes Rooooooooooooooooooooooootttttttt! What a champion cricketer!!! The decision to not take the second new ball immediately has worked. Australia are still 54 runs away but now they have only two wickets left. Coming to the delivery, it's tossed up around off, Alex Carey wears his skates to hammer it over and behind the bowler but fails to connect properly. It hurries back to Root who sticks both his hands together and this time grabs a sharp reflex catch. Root gets up and starts to run in joy. Carey is distraught, he has given England a massive opening.

Commentary: FOUR! AUSTRALIA WIN! Pat Cummins is pumped up, he lifts Lyon in delight. What an end to this Test match! The 8th wicket partnership has done it for the tourists. Back of a length, around off, Cummins pushes inside the line with soft hands and edges it down towards third man. Harry Brook speeds across to his right from straightish third man and Zak Crawley chases it to his left from deep point. Brook reaches first with a slide but he ends up deflecting it over the fence. Australia win by 2 wickets and have excelled in their first assignment against England's 'Bazball'!
